Prosper Loan Data¶

Analysis done by: Zahra Al-Hourani¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This dataset is financial and related to the Loan, Borrowers, Lenders, Interest rates, etc. Prosper or Prosper Marketplace Inc. is a San Francisco, California-based company specializing in loans at low-interest rates to borrowers. In this dataset, we are using the data from Prosper to analyze it and trying to find the pattern in the Prosper data.

The dataset is comprised of 81 variables and contains 113937 entries.

The data has a lot of null values. So, I can not drop the rows that contain a null value. I will use the simplest type of interpolation is the linear interpolation, which makes a mean between values before the missing data and a value after.

In [7]:
#Create a new copy of table 
ProsperLoans_Copy = ProsperLoans.copy()
In [8]:
#This function to replace NaN with Linear Interpolation
#I will use this function for 'EstimatedEffectiveYield' , 'EstimatedLoss' , 'EstimatedReturn' columns
def Interpolation(x):
    values= ProsperLoans_Copy[x].mean()
    Interpolation_of_Values = ProsperLoans_Copy.fillna(value=values,inplace = True)
    return Interpolation_of_Values
#This function will return mean value in each cell that contain NaN
In [9]:

#'EstimatedReturn'

Interpolation('EstimatedReturn')

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset is comprised of 14 variables and contains 113937 entries. Most variables are numeric (int, float), other variables (object) and (bool).

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main interest is to figure out What factors affect a borrower Rate, borrower APR, Loan Status.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

  • I expect that the 'Term' and 'EstimatedReturn' effect on the 'BorrowerAPR' of the loan.
  • I expect that the 'IsBorrowerHomeowner' will also have effects on the 'BowrrowerRate'.
  • I expect 'LoanStatus' have a relation with 'LenderYeild', 'BowrrowerAPR' and' BowrrowerRate'.
  • I expect that the 'ProsperScore' have a relation with 'BowrrowerAPR'.
  • I expect that the 'LenderYield' have a relation with 'BorrowerRate' and 'LoanStatus'.

#Just compare the string to whatever I expect to accept as representing True and
#Checks against a whole bunch of values
def str_to_bool(v):
    return str(v).lower() in ("yes", "true", "True", "1")
#This distripution plot to show if the brrower have home or not

#This function to plot all box plots 
def AllBoxPlot (df,xVar,yVar):
    
    sns.boxplot(data=df.sort_values(by=xVar), x=yVar, y=xVar, orient='h').set_title(f'{yVar} vs {xVar}' , fontsize='x-large')
#Use this code to define the boundaries of the chart
    plt.gcf().set_size_inches(14 , 8)
#Use this code to put the title and its proparities
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {yVar} by {xVar}'.title(), fontsize = 14 , weight = "bold")
#Use this code to put x and labeles and its proparities 
    plt.xlabel(yVar.title(), fontsize= 10, weight = "bold")
    plt.ylabel(xVar.title(), fontsize= 10, weight = "bold");
